{"id":8047,"date":"2017-11-03T08:07:00","date_gmt":"2017-11-03T15:07:00","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/?p=8047"},"modified":"2024-01-02T23:39:27","modified_gmt":"2024-01-03T07:39:27","slug":"red-mountain-toad-mountain-copper-mountain","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2017\/11\/03\/red-mountain-toad-mountain-copper-mountain\/","title":{"rendered":"RED MOUNTAIN, TOAD MOUNTAIN &#038; COPPER MOUNTAIN"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><em><strong>TOAD MT<\/strong><\/em>\u00a0 \u00a02209m 7247&#8242;<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><em><strong>RED MT<\/strong><\/em>\u00a0 \u00a02183m 7159&#8242;<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><em><strong>COPPER MT<\/strong><\/em>\u00a0 2190m 7200&#8242;<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><em>These 3 minor mountains share a four-kilometre long, NE to SW trending ridge. The summit of Toad Mountain is 10 kilometres SSW of downtown Nelson. Red Mt and Toad Mt are close neighbours and often summitted on the same trip. Climbing has some route-finding and bushwhacking.<br \/>\nCopper Mountain and its hut are part of the Bonnington Traverse.\u00a0<\/em><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Difficulty:<\/strong> B2 moderate<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Distance:<\/strong> Red Mt 4.6 km one way. Toad Mt 3.4 km one way. <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Elevation:\u00a0<\/strong>Red Mt +491m. Toad Mt +370 m <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Season:<\/strong>\u00a0early July to late September<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Map:<\/strong>\u00a082F\/6 Nelson<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Drive. <\/strong>Giveout Creek FSR is the same road access as Toad Mountain. From Nelson, drive south on Hwy 6, and turn right on GCR, just before Cottonwood Regional Park\/Lake. <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>0.0<\/strong> Turn up Giveout Creek FSR. <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">1.6 km. Ignore the switchback leading left<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">4.8 km. Cross a bridge over Giveout Creek. <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">9.0 km. Pass the upper kiosk for the Morning Mountain Bike Trails.\u00a0<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">10.0 km. A major junction \u2013 go left up the west branch of Giveout Creek FSR. Continue on switchbacks on the main road up the bowl below Toad Mountain. <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">16.7km. Park at the forked junction near the top of the ridge<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Trail.<br \/>\nRed Mountain.<\/strong> Hike a loop using a bushwhack shortcut up the ridge, and come back on the Upper Powerslave mountain bike trail.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Walk up the logging road to the left angling up towards Toad Mountain. As the road fizzles out in a clearcut, follow the flagged shortcut route to the ridge.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">0.7km. The trail fizzles out. Continue southwest along the forest edge looking for flagging tape and an arrow-marked log to enter the forest.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">1.0 km. Cross 2 rockslides.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">1.2 km. A short steep slope full of alder.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">1.5 km. Reach the top of the ridge where the shortcut route meets the official Upper Powerslave Trail that is used to access Toad Mountain. Turn left south for 400m of easy, flat trail walking. <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">1.9km. Look for more flagging tape and another rough route on the right, the turn-off to Red Mountain and the <\/span><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">red rock of the summit.<br \/>\n<\/span><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><em><strong>Return<\/strong><\/em> left on the mountain bike trail and hike down Toad\u2019s northern ridge for a more gradual descent. Exit the Upper Powerslave Trail at 8km on another logging road, and turn right through the clearcuts and your vehicle.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>From Red Mt to Toad Mt<\/strong> ~1.5km, <\/span><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Descend 650&#8242; to the col (6500&#8242;) and ascend 750&#8242; to the summit of Toad.<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>From Red Mt to Copper Mt<\/strong> ~3.5kms, 3 bumps on a ridge<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Copper Mountain <\/strong>2190m (7200&#8242;)<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Drive.<\/strong> From Nelson drive west on Hwy 3A. Turn left before the Hwy 3A bridge onto Blewett Road<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">1. At Blewett, turn left (south) on\u00a0 May and Jenny Road (Copper Mt FSR) up 49 Creek. 25 km on a bumpy road. The road ascends towards Red Mountain.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">2. Rover Creek FSR:<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">10 km Go straight. Right goes up Snowwater Creek<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">14 km Park (5400\u2019) on Snowwater Ck.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Route:<\/strong> Climb to the NE ridge of Mt Connor, then over the cirque below the north face. From ridge ski north into headwaters of Eric Ck. Climb through trees to the east ridge of Copper Mt.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Mt.Connor<\/strong> 3kms (as the crow flies) WWN of Copper Mt. Bypassed to south.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Rover Ck Rd &#8211;\u00a0<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Snowwater Ck \u2013 14.5 to Snowwater Creek 5400&#8242;.<\/span><\/span><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>TOAD MT\u00a0 \u00a02209m 7247&#8242; RED MT\u00a0 \u00a02183m 7159&#8242; COPPER MT\u00a0 2190m 7200&#8242; These 3 minor mountains share a four-kilometre long, NE to SW trending ridge. The summit of Toad Mountain is 10 kilometres SSW of downtown Nelson. Red Mt and &hellip; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2017\/11\/03\/red-mountain-toad-mountain-copper-mountain\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"jetpack_post_was_ever_published":false,"_jetpack_newsletter_access":"","_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs":false,"_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id":0,"_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content":false,"_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content":false,"footnotes":"","jetpack_publicize_message":"","jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled":true,"jetpack_social_post_already_shared":true,"jetpack_social_options":{"image_generator_settings":{"template":"highway","default_i